# Project Base Rules

## Rule Scope

- Defines permitted technologies and mandatory conventions
- Does not define folder structure or naming (see `architecture.mdc`)
- Does not define how to build Design System components (see `design-system-components.mdc`)

## Framework

### Next.js 16 with App Router

- **Default**: Server Components for all components
- **Client Components** (`'use client'`) only when:
  - Animation depends on state or interaction
  - Direct user interaction required (event handlers, inputs)
  - External library explicitly requires it (see `custom-library.mdc`)
- Always justify `'use client'` usage
- Keep Client Components as isolated leaf nodes

## Styling

### Tailwind CSS v4

- Primary and mandatory styling system
- Traditional CSS not allowed for layout or common styles
- Native CSS only permitted for:
  - `@keyframes` animations
  - Custom Properties (`--variables`)
  - Visual effects that cannot be expressed with Tailwind
- Never hardcode visual values outside the token system

## Animations

### Motion

- Primary library for all animations — no alternatives allowed
- CSS animations only permitted when:
  - No state required
  - Purely decorative
  - No complex interaction dependency

## Carousels

### Embla (via internal CLI)

- Only permitted carousel system
- Swiper, Slick, and all alternatives are prohibited
- Complex carousels must use the internal library implementation

## Forms and Validation

### Zod

- Mandatory for form validation, data schemas, and input validation
- Complex validation logic requires an explicit schema definition

## Package Manager

### PNPM

- Mandatory — npm and yarn are not allowed

## Internal Libraries

### Company CLI (`@androbinco/library-cli`)

- All primary UI tools (animations, carousels, overlays, etc.) must come from the internal CLI
- Some components use Radix UI as a base — do not use Radix UI directly
- Consume only through CLI-provided components (see `custom-library.mdc`)
